Video Game Creation Syllabus 
(this syllabus is a working document and changes can be requested on GitHub as students may have ideas on how to make this class more relevant and better!)

Explore video game development, including game design, gameplay development, and asset creation. 
Students will submit their game they developed in a video game competition in the fall.

Week 1: Explore Games That Work - Genres, Strategies, Storylines, Rules
Week 2: Game Components - Characters, Tokens, Scores, Objectives
Week 3: Platforms - Explore Scratch, Godot, Unity
